3 Sec. 4. 1. The Governor shall annually proclaim the first day of the
4 month of Vaisakh of the Sikh calendar to be “Vaisakhi Day” in the State of
5 Nevada.
6 2. The proclamation may call upon the news media, educators, business
7 and labor leaders and appropriate governmental officers to bring to the attention
8 of the residents of Nevada the diversity and inclusion of the cultures that
9 celebrate Vaisakhi in the State of Nevada and throughout the world.
10 Sec. 5. 1. The Governor shall annually proclaim the day of the first full
11 moon in the month of May to be “Vesak Day,” also known as “Buddha Day,” in
12 the State of Nevada.
13 2. The proclamation may call upon the news media, educators, business
14 and labor leaders and appropriate governmental officers to bring to the attention
15 of the residents of Nevada the diversity and inclusion of the cultures that
16 celebrate Vesak in the State of Nevada and throughout the world.
17 Sec. 6. This act becomes effective upon passage and approval.

